<p>This is my code:</p>  <pre><code>def issorted(numlist):     sortbool = True     for i in range(1, len(numlist)):         if numlist[i] &lt; numlist[i-1]:             sortbool = False             if True:               return(not sortbool)     return(sortbool) </code></pre>  <p>How do I put at least one more return statement? This is so that it can abort the function prematurely when a local violation of the sort-order requirement is detected. </p>  <p>The example of the output given are:</p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; print(issorted([3, 4, 5.0, 7])) True &gt;&gt;&gt; print(issorted([-1, 8, -3, 8])) False &gt;&gt;&gt; print(issorted([1])) True &gt;&gt;&gt; print(issorted([])) True </code></pre>